text: Overall a nice place, service is nice and food is served fast. Food quality isn’t bad and it’s considered affordable for a bar setting. God vibes but the music can be very loud.

Great place to hang with friends with good tasting and affordable drinks, good music too!
Provides free dice to play simple games.

Helen’s offers a diverse menu, providing options for various tastes and dietary preferences. The restaurant has a warm and inviting ambience, ideal for casual dining or special occasions. The staff is generally attentive and helpful, enhancing the dining experience. The food quality can vary, with some dishes lacking flavor or proper seasoning. Service may be slow, particularly during busy periods, leading to long waits. The restaurant can feel cramped, making it less comfortable, especially during peak times.
Nice little hidden gem. opens til late. Audience is in their early 20s.
